<paragraph pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<bibRefCitation author="Ausserer, A" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft (Wien)" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="125 - 206" title="Zweiter Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Arachniden-Familie der Territelariae Thorell (Mygalidae Autor)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/16420158page/229/mode/1up" volume="25" year="1875">Ausserer (1875)</bibRefCitation>
described a male with two-branched tibial apophysis, and having setae on palpal tibia. It resembles a theraphosine specimen, but Ausserer did not give information on diagnostic characters. Thus, we consider 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Avicularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Avicularia rapax" order="Araneae" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapax">Avicularia rapax</taxonomicName>
(Ausserer, 1875) a nomen dubium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
We failed to find holotypes of both 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pertyâ€™s">Perty's</normalizedToken>
species below. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Perty, JAM" editor="von Spix, JB" journalOrPublisher="Monachii" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="191 - 209" title="Arachnides Brasilienses" url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.102991" volumeTitle="Delectus animalium articulatorum quae in itinere per Brasiliam annis MDCCXVII-MDCCCXX jussu et auspiciis Maximiliani Josephi I. Bavariae Regis Augustissimi, percato collegerunt Dr. J. B. de Spix et Dr. C. F. Ph. de Martius, 1830 - 1834" year="1833">Perty (1833)</bibRefCitation>
drew in detail the legs of these species, showing well-developed scopulae on tarsi and metatarsi, with the spatulated aspect characteristic of aviculariines.
</paragraph>
